.  aThis book offers insights into the methods of research on scientific language and scientific prose – the two basic research approaches for studying specialized historical texts. It presents analyses of medieval and early modern texts drawn from different subfields to document both traditional methodology and newer options for research made possible by recent technological advances.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aGerman languagexTechnical GermanvCongresses. 0aGerman languageyEarly modern, 1500-1700xWord formationvCongresses. 0aGerman languageyMiddle High German, 1050-1500xWord formationvCongresses. 0aGerman literatureyMiddle High German, 1050-1500xHistory and criticismvCongresses. 4aFachsprache. 4aPragmatik (Sprache). 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aPragmatics (language).  aTerminology.1 aAdamson, Melitta Weiss, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBily, Inge, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBok, Václav, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrom, Vlastimil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChlench, Kathrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHabermann, Mechthild, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHünecke, Rainer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKeil, Gundolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlein, Wolf Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMayer, Johannes Gottfried, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSpáčilová, Libuše, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVanková, Lenka, eeditor.4edt4